  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD pipeline relies on a multi-threaded finite-volume solver with parallel domain decomposition and an in-house hemolysis post-processing script. Solver robustness was studied informally during development; all production simulation runs completed nominally. No systematic evaluation of numerical instability, race conditions in the parallel solver, or edge-case crash modes was performed.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-cfd-identifies-worst-case-hemolysis",
